{
  "doc_id": "17149",
  "text": "Three sets of sentinels from flocks DM, TR, and NG had small numbers of viral reads with homology to the avian picobirnaviruses (PBVs). The PBVs were detected and described in a recent metagenomic analysis of the turkey gut viral metagenome [CITATION_1] , and have been described in chicken flocks as well [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . As has been noted in all avian PBVs to date, the PBVs in the present analysis all appear to be members of the PBV genogroup I [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
